text: So I actually saw this at SXSW, and I feel the need to explain a few things. All of you who are saying "not liking the dead wife cliche"...without spoiling things, yeah, that's kind of the point. There is more to the story than meets the eye. All I can say is, PLEASE, see this movie. Everyone in the theater gave it an energetic standing ovation IMMEDIATELY when the credits started rolling. If any modern movie deserves your money, it's this one.

text: Probably the most ridiculous movie I've seen, the script is a joke and totally predictable from the first minute. Basically the main character is implanted with a sort like HAL 9000 AI that interacts internally with him, then you see car chases, fights and the victory of the evil AI over the mankind at the end. The character development is null but apparently what appeals to many people, a bearded mechanic, a lovely wife, an introverted mad geek and a former soldier that was subject to experiments, oh and an androgynous hacker which best line is "You're the one wasting time putting me in a binary box". The acting is also very crappy and the dialogs a bag of cliches. But hey there are good and bad guys, car chases, fights an intrinsic apprehension to technology and a vindication of all that make us humans so special, can't fail.

You will get the same feeling after watching "Upgrade". If you like sci-fi movies like Ex Machina, The Terminator, RoboCop (original) and The Matrix, then you will love this movie. It was also made for only $5 million dollars! Venom was made for $100 + million, and despite a similar premise (and similar looking lead actors) "Upgrade" is the superior movie by far. 9/10!
